('2177', '1', 'Heat oven to 450 F. In a medium bowl, combine the potato, zucchini, scallions, oil,  teaspoon salt, and  teaspoon pepper.Divide the vegetables among 4 12- to 15-inch pieces of parchment.'),
('2177', '2', 'Place the fish over each pile of vegetables and top with the lemon slices, olives, and thyme.Fold the parchment over the fish, then seal each packet by making small overlapping folds along the edges.'),
('2177', '3', 'Place on 2 baking sheets and bake for 20 minutes.'),
('2178', '1', 'Wash and dry catfish filets.'),
('2178', '2', 'Place filets in a shallow dish and pour milk over them. Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.'),
('2178', '3', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cheese, Italian seasoning, baking powder, garlic powder, dry mustard, onion powder, salt and pepper. Dredge filets in flour mixture.'),
('2178', '4', 'Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet and place coated filets in pan.'),
('2178', '5', 'Drizzle melted butter over filets.'),
('2178', '6', 'Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until firm and flaky.'),
('2178', '7', 'Serve hot.'),
('2179', '1', 'Soak 8 wooden skewers in a large bowl of water for 10 minutes.'),
('2179', '2', 'Heat broiler.Alternating, thread the fish, tomatoes, bell pepper, and mushrooms onto the skewers, ending each with a lime wedge.'),
('2179', '3', 'Place the skewers on a rimmed baking sheet and toss with the oil, oregano, and  teaspoon salt.Broil the skewers until the fish is cooked through and the vegetables are slightly charred, 3 to 4 minutes per side.'),
('2180', '1', 'Heat a large griddle or nonstick skillet with cooking spray and set over medium-high heat. Season tomatoes with salt and black pepper and add to hot pan. Cook 1 minute per side, flipping with a spatula, until golden brown.'),
('2180', '2', 'Remove from heat.'),
('2180', '3', 'In a small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, basil, chives, mustard, and lemon zest.'),
('2180', '4', 'Spread mixture on rolls. Top with seared tomatoes, catfish, lettuce leaves, and red onion.'),
('2181', '1', 'In a mixing bowl, stir together cornmeal, cayenne pepper, paprika and onion powder.'),
('2181', '2', 'Mix well.'),
('2181', '3', 'Pour mixture onto a large sheet of waxed paper.'),
('2181', '4', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('2181', '5', 'Pour milk into a medium bowl. Dip catfish filets into milk and hold up and let the milk drip off.'),
('2181', '6', 'Roll the milk-soaked filet in the cornmeal mixture until completely covered. Set aside.'),
('2181', '7', 'Fry the garlic in the hot skillet, but do not burn.'),
('2181', '8', 'Add the coated catfish filets and cook for 5 to 7 minutes on each side, sprinkling salt on the fish after each turn. Cook until golden brown and fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('2181', '9', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
